						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ••••• Year: ••••</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Śivaṉāchchāri, son of Vīrararāchāri, a metal smith <hi rend="italic">(karumāṉ)</hi> who possessed <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> in Muttukkūṟ and Selvāchāri, son of Aṅgāchāri, caused the construction of steps <hi rend="italic">(sōpāna).</hi> It is also mentioned that both of them were the carpenters of Kōmūr.</p>						

						<p>This inscription on the grounds of palaeography may be assigned to the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
